e’s flame steadies and points toward the abbot’s cell do you move, stepping away as one steps away from a cliff’s edge in a story told to children who are meant to keep breathing.\", \"outcome\": \"The market’s warm exhalation cools into mere draft, and a hint of resin and mothwax rides it, a sign that the Quiet Wing’s refusal has been heard without offense. A thread of sound uncoils from deep within the ruined organ, not a lure but a direction, and it guides you toward a wall-stone that surrenders the chart with the gratitude of a patient dismissed. Seler’s face loses the strained brightness of someone who is almost sold, and he thanks you without voice, saving the thanks for the Archive where words are paid their due in order. The candle gutters as you leave, not from wind but from completion, and you pinch it out with two fingers so as not to promise it further work. No debt is incurred but vigilance, and vigilance is a debt you are willing to carry because it lightens rather than weighs; the path back opens like a door that recognizes good manners.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C3\", \"title\": \"Parley with the cliff scavengers under Compact courtesy\", \"text\": \"When Ysil Kett and her pickers step from the fresco shadows with their lanterns hooded to a bargaining glow, you lower your sabre but not your guard and greet them by the Ropes and Knots Hall’s dock-etiquette. You name the bell-chart as civic salvage already sworn to the Archive, and you name yourself responsible for its safe return, putting your reputation where the law cannot reach. You offer them a safer descent path marked by Warden code, a whisper of an untouched kiln-stair on the south face, and a writ-tokened promise of first look at any legal work moving through the Quiet Walks that needs hands without questions. You speak to their hunger like to a neighbor’s thirst, acknowledging it as honest but refusing to turn the well into a private cup, and you remind them that blood on the stairs makes a poor profit. When their hands loosen, you share dried saffron bread and the story of one gate opening too fast, and between bites and the weather the edge of the moment dulls to something that need not cut.\", \"outcome\": \"Ysil Kett decides that a clean corridor is worth more than a noisy quarrel, and she counts your offers not as coin but as routes to future coin, which is the better arithmetic. The scavengers pocket their hooks without making you bleed for the privilege, and they melt back into the mural’s moth-swarmed gloom, leaving a small cairn to warn you of a loose stair three turns ahead. Your promise becomes a cord around your wrist that you can feel when you sleep, a new knot among the others, but it sits light because it was tied in daylight. Seler breathes easier and does not meet your eye until his cheeks have learned not to show relief, and then he nods as if to admit that talking can be a weapon when a blade would be a mistake. The city will remember that the chart reached the Archive without a fight, and the city’s memory is a market that actually opens every dawn, which is the sort worth investing in.\"\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M6\"], \"next\": [\"M8\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"faction favor\", \"description\": \"Order of Moths favor (major): formal permission to consult the Hall of Unnumbered Calendars and its shifting dates without a chaperone.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"item\", \"description\": \"A windline token from Mira Cael, tuned to Warden sky-kite code; when shown or sounded, it signals emergency aerial extraction to friendly skiffs.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"insight\", \"description\": \"Understanding that the palimpsest, once steadied by the bell-chart, marks a lightwell widening beneath the Prism Spire, a danger pressing closer each new moon.\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"